T: The Hope
W:
W: Into the world came a new feeling,
W:    through the world goes a powerful call;
W: on the wings of a gentle wind
W:    let it now fly from place to place.
W: Not to the sword thirsting for blood
W:    does it draw the human family:
W: to the world eternally at war
W:    it promises sacred harmony.
W:
W:  ...
W:
W: Under the sacred sign of hope
W:    gather the warriors of peace,
W: and this thing quickly grows
W:    by the labors of those who hope.
W: The walls of millennia stand firm
W:    between the divided peoples;
W: but the stubborn barriers will crumble,
W:    knocked down with sacred love.
W:
W:  ...
W:
W: Based on a neutral language,
W:    understanding one another,
W: the people will agree to make
W:    one great family circle.
W: Our diligent colleagues
W:    in peaceful labor will never tire,
W: until the beautiful dream of humanity
W:    for eternal good is realized.
